<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🎮 RB005 Week 2 — English Worksheet</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Greybox It — Find the Fun First · <strong>Course:</strong> Dream Game Studio · <strong>Time:</strong> about 45 minutes</p>
<p>This week you build your WHOLE map with plain gray parts. No colors, no decorations, no fancy models. This is called <strong>greyboxing</strong> — it lets you find the fun fast, before you spend hours making things pretty.</p>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read each situation. Write what you think before class.</p>
<p><strong>A student spends the whole first week decorating a beautiful start area. In week 3 they finally playtest — and the game is boring. What went wrong with their order of work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Your greybox map is ugly, but you can already play it from start to goal in 2 minutes. Why is this MORE useful right now than a beautiful map you cannot play yet?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>During a playtest you find a jump that is too easy, so a whole section is boring. Your parts are plain gray boxes. How hard is it to move them around? What if that section were already fully decorated?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Spot the Problem 🐛</h2>
<p>Each layout plan below is broken. Read what the plan is <strong>supposed</strong> to do, then explain what is wrong and how you would fix it.</p>
<p><strong>Plan A</strong> — The player should play from start to finish.</p>
<pre><code>START platform → big open field → ???
</code></pre>
<p><strong>The player spawns, runs around the field … and then what? What is missing? Where would you put it?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Plan B</strong> — The game should take a few minutes and feel like a challenge.</p>
<pre><code>START platform → GOAL flag (3 steps away)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>A player wins in 3 seconds without doing anything. What is missing in the middle? What would you add?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Now sketch YOUR layout below.</strong> Mark the START, the GOAL, and draw the path the player takes between them.</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Tell Me What You Built 📸</h2>
<p>Now open Roblox Studio and greybox your WHOLE layout from your week 1 design — start, path, goal — all in plain gray parts. Then playtest it for 10 minutes. When you finish, come back here.</p>
<p>Send a photo or video of your greybox map, then explain what you found. Use these sentence starters — write 4 to 6 sentences total.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>My greybox map has …</p>
<p>The player starts at … and wins by …</p>
<p>In my playtest, the fun part was …</p>
<p>The boring part was …</p>
<p>After playtesting, I changed … because …</p>
<p>Before I decorate, I still want to fix …</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Record Your Walkthrough 🎥</h2>
<p>Now take a video on your phone (or a parent's phone) while you walk through your greybox map in Studio. Narrate the player's path like a tour guide. Try to use these words: <strong>greybox</strong>, <strong>layout</strong>, <strong>start</strong>, <strong>goal</strong>, <strong>playtest</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<ol>
<li>Start at the spawn and walk the path a player would take.</li>
<li>Point at the goal and say the win condition.</li>
<li>Show the most fun part and say why it is fun.</li>
<li>Show one thing you changed after your playtest.</li>
</ol>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write what you will say in your video.</strong> Use the space below to plan it before you record — you can read from it while filming.</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your walkthrough video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
